title: Shift summary: Monday swing
text: SUMMARY: Accelerator physics all shift. INJECTOR: Up as needed for injection, 150-300mV Q. The PR-2 camera had to be rebooted (0Hz rate problem). SPEAR: The BL15 instability program ended early. The BTS tuning program proceeded per schedule. BSOIC S23 tripped twice during trajectory scans, so the chopper rate was lowered to 5Hz. Unfortunately, the 5Hz rate correlated to an occasional NaN reading for BTS BPM4. The scan code was modified to pause at certain points, which allowed the chopper to run at 10Hz without tripping the BSOIC. The TRIBs program is still in progress at the end of the shift. This uses a 6nm lattice, and beamline 2 is open for pinhole camera data. The SPEAR kickers were found in single shot mode twice during the TRIBs program, possibly due to the programâs Matlab script.
